Why this note is important

When working in AWS, it’s very common to create:

One VPC for bastion (public access)
Another VPC for secure/private workloads

By default, these VPCs are completely isolated — even inside the same account.

👉 That’s why this issue happens:

SSH works within same VPC ✅
SSH fails across VPCs ❌ (even if SG + keypair are correct)

So this note helps you remember:

“Whenever two VPCs need to communicate → I must configure peering + routing + security”

🧠 Scenario
VPC-1 (Bastion) → 10.0.0.0/16
VPC-2 (Private EC2) → 10.1.0.0/16

Goal:
👉 Bastion → SSH → Private EC2 (in another VPC)

✅ Step-by-Step Process (Follow This Always)
🔹 STEP 1: Create VPC Peering
Go to VPC Dashboard
Click Peering Connections
Click Create Peering Connection
Select:
Requester → Bastion VPC
Accepter → Private VPC
Create
🔹 STEP 2: Accept Peering
Go to Peering Connections
Select request
Click:
👉 Actions → Accept Request

✅ Status must be: Active

🔥 STEP 3: Update Route Tables (MOST IMPORTANT)

Without this → ❌ NOTHING works

🟦 Bastion VPC Route Table (Public RT)

Add route:

Destination: 10.1.0.0/16
Target: VPC Peering (pcx-xxxx)
🟩 Private VPC Route Table (Private RT)

Add route:

Destination: 10.0.0.0/16
Target: VPC Peering (pcx-xxxx)
🔐 STEP 4: Security Group Configuration
On Private EC2:
Type: SSH
Port: 22
Source: 10.0.0.0/16   (Bastion VPC CIDR)
🔹 STEP 5: (Optional but Important) NACL Check

Make sure:

Inbound → Allow SSH + ephemeral ports (1024–65535)
Outbound → Allow ALL
🧪 STEP 6: Test Connectivity

From bastion:

ping 10.1.x.x
ssh -i key.pem ubuntu@10.1.x.x
🚨 Common Mistakes (VERY IMPORTANT)

❌ Only creating peering → not enough
❌ Forgetting route tables ← MOST COMMON ISSUE
❌ Using wrong route table (not attached to subnet)
❌ Wrong CIDR in routes
❌ Security group blocking SSH

🧠 Quick Mental Checklist

Whenever SSH fails across VPC:

✔ Peering = Active
✔ Route (VPC-1 → VPC-2)
✔ Route (VPC-2 → VPC-1)
✔ SG allows correct CIDR
✔ Correct subnet route table

🎯 One-line Summary

Two VPCs cannot communicate by default — you must enable it using VPC Peering + Route Tables + Security Groups
